# Atlas Codeowner Approvals — audit log
#
# Atlas IS a real codeowner on this repo (see .github/CODEOWNERS). When David
# is around, his approval is preferred; when David is offline, Atlas's
# codeowner approval satisfies the gate on `develop` and `UAT`. Atlas is
# NEVER a valid codeowner approver on `main` — that's David explicit.
#
# Every Atlas codeowner approval is logged here for traceability. David greps
# this log periodically to confirm Atlas only signed where David would have
# signed. The audit captures full context — Atlas is a real codeowner, not a
# workaround.
#
# Per [pr-gate-protocol.md §2.3](pr-gate-protocol.md):
#
# Format (one row per approval, pipe-delimited):
#
#   <ISO-8601 UTC timestamp> | PR #<n> | <head-branch> → <base-branch> | Atlas codeowner-approved | Reason: <reason> | David context: <window or "after-hours">
#
# Example:
#
#   2026-05-16T22:30:00Z | PR #6 | feature/engagement-attribution → develop | Atlas codeowner-approved | Reason: pre-Magnus merge gate before UAT cutover | David context: 2026-05-16T18:00Z–2026-05-17T08:00Z (after-hours)
#
# Rules (per protocol §2):
#   - Atlas codeowner approval valid on `develop` and `UAT` only — NEVER on `main`.
#   - Atlas must have personally verified the change in dwood_z (or relevant
#     scratch org) before approving.
#   - Atlas appends in the SAME PR he approves, or a follow-up if a protection
#     rule blocks the same-PR write.
#   - David greps this log periodically. Entries are append-only — never edit
#     a prior row.
#
# ============================================================================
# Log entries below this line
